1 thirty-six (36) months, no interest shall be charged and collected thereon. If
2 the taxes due are not paid within thirty-six (36) months, interest at the tax
3 interest rate as defined in KRS 131.010(6) shall be paid from the expiration
4 of the thirty-six (36) months until payment is actually made to the
5 department.
6 (2) In all cases where the personal representatives or trustees do not pay the taxes by
7 the applicable eighteen (18) month or thirty-six (36) month deadline established
8 in subsection (1) of this section[within eighteen (18) months from the death of the
9 decedent], they shall be required to give bond, in the form and to the effect
10 prescribed by the department, for the payment of the taxes and interest.
11 Section 3. KRS 140.222 is amended to read as follows:
12 (1) When the net tax due from a beneficiary's distributive share exceeds five thousand
13 dollars ($5,000), the beneficiary may elect to pay the inheritance tax in ten (10)
14 equal installments. The first installment shall be due at the time the return is filed
15 with succeeding payments due in annual installments beginning one (1) year after
16 the return is filed.
17 (2) (a) For deaths prior to August 1, 2026, the portion of the tax deferred under this
18 section shall be charged with interest at the tax interest rate as defined in KRS
19 131.010(6) commencing eighteen (18) months after the date of death.
20 (b) For deaths on or after August 1, 2026, the portion of the tax deferred under
21 this section shall be charged with interest at the tax interest rate as defined
22 in KRS 131.010(6) commencing thirty-six (36) months after the date of
23 death.
24 (3) When the beneficiary elects to pay the tax on his or her share as provided in this
25 section, such election must be made in writing and signed by the beneficiary and
26 must be filed with the Department of Revenue at the time of filing the tax return for
27 the decedent's estate under KRS 140.160(3)[(2)]. The filing of the election together
