1 with payment of the first installment shall relieve the personal representative or
2 trustee of the estate from further liability for the tax payments deferred under this
3 section and the bond requirements of KRS 140.210, subject to the final approval by
4 the Department of Revenue of all other taxes due under this chapter.
5 (4) A beneficiary electing to defer the payment of taxes under this section shall be
6 personally liable for the amount of deferred taxes until paid.
7 (5) The period of limitations for actions to enforce the collection of taxes imposed by
8 this chapter as provided by KRS 140.160(4)[(3)] shall be suspended for the period
9 of time for deferred payment granted by this section.
